  "prompt": "I do not have a surname on passport or any of my education certificates. What should be the most appropriate step now to fix the issue?",
  "response": "If you do not have a surname on your passport or any of your education certificates, here are the steps you can take to address the issue:\n\n1. **Verify Naming Conventions**: First, confirm your country\u2019s naming conventions regarding surnames. In some cultures, a surname may not be used, or there may be alternative naming conventions.\n\n2. **Contact Relevant Authorities**:\n   - **Passport Office**: Reach out to the passport issuing authority in your country to inquire about the procedures to add a surname to your passport. They may need you to provide specific documents or proof of identity.\n   - **Educational Institutions**: Contact the administration or registrar's office of any educational institutions from which you received certificates. Ask them about the process to amend your name on those documents.\n\n3. **Gather Supporting Documents**: Prepare any documents that may support your request for name changes, such as birth certificates, legal documents, or any identification that verifies your identity and naming convention.\n\n4. **Legal Name Change**: If it is necessary or helpful, consider formally changing your name through legal means. Check the process in your jurisdiction for legally changing your name, as this may provide you with a consistent name to use across all documents.\n\n5. **Consistent Naming**: Choose the name format you wish to adopt going forward (e.g., first name only, first name with surname), and aim to use this consistently in all future applications and documents.\n\n6. **Keep Records**: Maintain copies of all correspondence and documents sent and received during this process for your records.\n\n7. **Consult a Legal Expert**: If you encounter difficulties or if there are complexities in your situation, consider consulting a legal expert to understand your rights and options.\n\n8. **Follow Up**: After submitting requests or applications, follow up with relevant authorities to ensure that your changes are processed in a timely manner.\n\nBy taking these steps, you can work toward resolving the issue of not having a surname on your documents.",
